38:08.488 --> 38:13.014
And the auctioneer, glad to get rid of this thing, put the hammer down and said, sold.

38:14.096 --> 38:22.748
At which point, very famous New York dealer named Papantonio, Michael Papantonio.

38:22.768 --> 38:26.313
He stands up and says, Mr. auctioneer, I am trying to buy that.

38:26.554 --> 38:27.495
I'm bidding on that article.

38:27.515 --> 38:30.880
And he said, ask my neighbors that I have been trying to get your attention.

38:31.552 --> 38:34.234
At which point, he jumps up.

38:34.975 --> 38:42.402
And one good thing, if he was on your side, at this time he was, he was a very gruff, bluff, and formidable opponent.

38:42.942 --> 38:46.705
He jumps up and he said, the hammer has fallen, I bought it for Mr. Self.

38:46.725 --> 38:49.108
And we consider the item sold.

38:49.888 --> 38:52.070
So the auctioneer was standing there not knowing what to do.

38:52.090 --> 38:53.291
