So I didn't know how to contact him, so I called Don Fleming from Los Angeles.

44:27.175 --> 44:29.598
And John, of course, was in New York.

44:29.618 --> 44:31.300
And I said, do you know this guy?

44:31.961 --> 44:33.884
I didn't want to call him the government.

44:35.105 --> 44:38.630
I thought he might not want me to get together with his clients.

44:38.650 --> 44:40.292
And that would be understandable.

44:40.312 --> 44:45.599
And so John was coming and said, the gentleman's name is Starling.

44:45.699 --> 44:48.302
And he was standing by my side.

44:49.283 --> 44:55.411
I said, I'm calling you 3,000 miles away about a guy that lives in Dayton, Ohio, and he's standing by your side.

44:55.491 --> 44:56.052
He said, yes.

44:56.926 --> 44:57.787
He said, do they put it on?

44:58.267 --> 44:59.248
So I said, this is about it.

44:59.268 --> 45:00.129
Isn't this okay?

45:00.349 --> 45:01.170
True.

45:01.190 --> 45:07.315
And I said, I'm from Dayton, Ohio, and I was at the Susan O'Sale, and I'd love to, we're coming to Dayton, and I'd love to see your collection.

45:07.335 --> 45:07.856
She said, by all means.

45:08.436 --> 45:09.097
So we make a date.

45:10.879 --> 45:24.090
Peggy and I went out, and it was a library, which would put my library to say, not only all the authors we've talked about, but this way, Thackeray, and Trollope, and all the modern... Conrad.

45:24.291 --> 45:26.933
Conrad, and the modern Hemingway, Faulkner,

45:27.318 --> 45:33.425
Well, our relationship really began about 1970.

45:33.445 --> 45:38.550
It's been 20 years, at least, that this happened.

